<div class="changelog">
<strong>Change Log (v10.0 &rarr; v10.1)</strong>
<ul>
<li>Removed <code>RefreshToken</code> and <code>RefreshTokenExpiry</code> columns from User table (simpler JWT-to-session approach adopted)</li>
<li>All status/type/role/category columns now use <strong>strongly-typed C# enums</strong> stored as strings via <code>HasConversion&lt;string&gt;()</code> &mdash; never integers</li>
<li>Enum values updated throughout all table definitions to match finalized codebase (see Section 5.7 for full enum reference)</li>
<li>Database migration strategy updated to <strong>single DbMigrator pattern</strong> &mdash; one <code>MigrationDbContext</code> creates all 25 tables atomically</li>
<li>Migration order table replaced with single-step DbMigrator command</li>
<li>Swagger configuration standardized across all 6 services (JsonStringEnumConverter + EnumSchemaFilter)</li>
</ul>
</div>

<h1>1. Introduction</h1>

<h2>1.1 What is EduLearn?</h2>
<p>EduLearn is an integrated platform for universities and colleges to manage student records, course delivery, assessments, timetables, faculty workflows, and accreditation reporting. It centralizes student profiles, enrollment, course catalogs, learning content, assessments, grades, billing, and audit logs so administrators, instructors, and students can operate with transparency, academic integrity, and regulatory compliance.</p>
<p>EduLearn supports deterministic enrollment rules, manual overrides, evidence capture for assessments, and exportable audit packages for accreditors. The platform replaces fragmented legacy systems (Canvas, Moodle, Blackboard) with a unified ecosystem covering the complete university operations lifecycle.</p>

<h2>1.2 Actors and Users</h2>
<table>
<tr><th>Role</th><th>Description</th><th>Key Capabilities</th></tr>
<tr><td>Student</td><td>Primary learner user</td><td>Enrolls in courses, accesses learning materials, submits assignments, views grades and bills</td></tr>
<tr><td>Instructor</td><td>Teaching faculty</td><td>Creates courses, delivers content, grades assessments, manages office hours</td></tr>
<tr><td>Registrar</td><td>Academic administration</td><td>Manages enrollment rules, timetables, transcripts, and graduation processing</td></tr>
<tr><td>Department Administrator</td><td>Department-level management</td><td>Configures course offerings, faculty assignments, and room allocations</td></tr>
<tr><td>Finance Officer</td><td>Financial operations</td><td>Issues invoices, records payments, manages scholarships and refunds</td></tr>
<tr><td>IT Administrator</td><td>System administration</td><td>Manages system configuration, integrations, backups, and security</td></tr>
<tr><td>Compliance Officer / Auditor</td><td>Regulatory compliance</td><td>Reviews academic records, grade changes, and audit packages</td></tr>
</table>

