</table>

<h2>1.4 Core Design Principles</h2>
<p>&bull; <strong>Curriculum Compliant:</strong> Every technology is from the Cognizant ADM DotNet FSE curriculum. No external AI/ML dependencies.</p>
<p>&bull; <strong>Deterministic Rules:</strong> Enrollment, prerequisites, graduation, and billing follow deterministic rule engines &mdash; transparent, testable, auditable.</p>
<p>&bull; <strong>Lean Schema:</strong> 25 entities with strategic JSON columns where full normalization adds complexity without query benefits.</p>
<p>&bull; <strong>Production Discipline:</strong> SonarQube, OWASP ZAP, structured logging, append-only audit logs from Day 1.</p>
<p>&bull; <strong>Evidence-Based:</strong> Assignments, recordings, transcripts stored in object storage with SHA-256 checksums for tamper evidence.</p>
<p>&bull; <strong>Regulatory Compliance:</strong> FERPA, GDPR ready with exportable audit packages for accreditors.</p>
<p>&bull; <strong>Strongly-Typed Enums:</strong> All status, type, role, and category fields use C# enums stored as strings in the database &mdash; no magic strings.</p>

