<h1>4. Microservice Architecture</h1>

<h2>4.1 Service Responsibilities</h2>
<table>
<tr><th>Service</th><th>Port</th><th>Modules Covered</th><th>Tables Owned</th></tr>
<tr><td>AuthService</td><td>5001</td><td>IAM</td><td>User, AuditLog</td></tr>
<tr><td>SISService</td><td>5002</td><td>SRA, ETS</td><td>Student, Applicant, Transcript, Section, Enrollment, Room</td></tr>
<tr><td>LMSService</td><td>5003</td><td>CCM, LMS, AGI</td><td>Course, Program, Syllabus, Content, Discussion, Assessment, Submission, GradeChange</td></tr>
<tr><td>AnalyticsService</td><td>5004</td><td>RKA</td><td>Report, KPI, AuditPackage</td></tr>
<tr><td>NotificationService</td><td>5005</td><td>NHT</td><td>Notification, Ticket</td></tr>
<tr><td>FinanceService</td><td>5006</td><td>SFB</td><td>FeeSchedule, Invoice, Payment, Scholarship</td></tr>
</table>

<h2>4.2 Communication Pattern</h2>
<p>React SPA &rarr; API Gateway (YARP or direct) &rarr; Individual Service &rarr; Shared Database. AnalyticsService reads data from tables owned by other services via read-only cross-service queries. NotificationService pushes events via SignalR Hub. FinanceService reads Student data from SIS-owned tables for invoice generation.</p>

<h2>4.3 Shared Database Strategy</h2>
<p>All 6 services connect to the same Azure SQL database (EduLearnDb). Each service has ownership over specific tables (only that service writes to its tables), but any service can read from any table. This avoids the complexity of database-per-service while maintaining logical separation. Entity Framework DbContext per service only includes the entity classes that service needs. Non-owned tables use <code>ExcludeFromMigrations()</code> to prevent duplicate schema creation.</p>

<h2>4.4 Module-to-Service Mapping</h2>
<table>
<tr><th>Module</th><th>Service</th><th>Rationale</th></tr>
<tr><td>IAM &mdash; Identity &amp; Access</td><td>AuthService</td><td>Standalone: auth logic is independent and security-critical</td></tr>
<tr><td>SRA &mdash; Student Registry</td><td>SISService</td><td>Shares Student entity with Enrollment module</td></tr>
<tr><td>ETS &mdash; Enrollment &amp; Timetable</td><td>SISService</td><td>Shares Student, Section entities with Registry</td></tr>
<tr><td>CCM &mdash; Course Catalog</td><td>LMSService</td><td>Shares Course entity with Content and Assessment</td></tr>
<tr><td>LMS &mdash; Learning Content</td><td>LMSService</td><td>Shares Course, Content entities with Catalog</td></tr>
<tr><td>AGI &mdash; Assessment &amp; Grading</td><td>LMSService</td><td>Shares Course, Submission entities with Content</td></tr>
<tr><td>SFB &mdash; Student Finance</td><td>FinanceService</td><td>Standalone: billing logic is isolated, references Student via FK</td></tr>
<tr><td>RKA &mdash; Reporting &amp; KPIs</td><td>AnalyticsService</td><td>Read-only: queries all services, writes only Report/KPI/AuditPackage</td></tr>
<tr><td>NHT &mdash; Notifications &amp; Helpdesk</td><td>NotificationService</td><td>Standalone: alerts + ticketing, SignalR hub</td></tr>
</table>

<h1>5. Database Schema (25 Entities)</h1>
<p>All entities reside in a single Azure SQL database (EduLearnDb) under the default dbo schema. JSON columns are used where query-by-column is not needed. Media files are stored in Azure Blob Storage; the database stores URIs and SHA-256 checksums for tamper evidence.</p>
<p><strong>Enum Storage Convention:</strong> All status, type, role, category, and method fields use strongly-typed C# enums with <code>HasConversion&lt;string&gt;()</code> in EF Core. Values are stored as <code>nvarchar</code> strings in the database (e.g., <code>"Active"</code>, <code>"Enrolled"</code>, <code>"Student"</code>), never as integers. See Section 5.7 for the complete enum reference.</p>

<h2>5.1 Entity Ownership by Service</h2>
<table>
<tr><th>Service</th><th>Tables Owned (Write)</th><th>Tables Referenced (Read-Only)</th></tr>
<tr><td>AuthService (:5001)</td><td>User, AuditLog</td><td>&mdash;</td></tr>
<tr><td>SISService (:5002)</td><td>Student, Applicant, Transcript, Section, Enrollment, Room</td><td>User, Course, Program</td></tr>
<tr><td>LMSService (:5003)</td><td>Course, Program, Syllabus, Content, Discussion, Assessment, Submission, GradeChange</td><td>User, Section, Student</td></tr>
<tr><td>AnalyticsService (:5004)</td><td>Report, KPI, AuditPackage</td><td>ALL tables (read-only)</td></tr>
<tr><td>NotificationService (:5005)</td><td>Notification, Ticket</td><td>User</td></tr>
<tr><td>FinanceService (:5006)</td><td>FeeSchedule, Invoice, Payment, Scholarship</td><td>Student, Program, User</td></tr>
</table>

<h2>5.2 Table Definitions</h2>

<h3>Module 1: Identity &amp; Access Management (AuthService)</h3>

<p><strong>1. User</strong></p>
<p><em>Authentication and identity for all 7 roles. PasswordHash uses BCrypt (cost=12). MFAEnabled flag for privileged roles.</em></p>
<table>
<tr><th>Column</th><th>Type</th><th>Constraints</th><th>Description</th></tr>
<tr><td>UserID</td><td>int</td><td>PK, Identity</td><td>Auto-increment primary key</td></tr>
<tr><td>Username</td><td>nvarchar(100)</td><td>Unique, Not Null</td><td>Login username</td></tr>
<tr><td>FullName</td><td>nvarchar(200)</td><td>Not Null</td><td>Display name</td></tr>
<tr><td>Email</td><td>nvarchar(255)</td><td>Unique, Not Null</td><td>Email address</td></tr>
<tr><td>Phone</td><td>nvarchar(20)</td><td>Nullable</td><td>Contact phone</td></tr>
<tr><td>Role</td><td>nvarchar(30)</td><td>Not Null, Enum: <code>UserRole</code></td><td>Student &verbar; Instructor &verbar; Registrar &verbar; DeptAdmin &verbar; Finance &verbar; ITAdmin &verbar; Auditor</td></tr>
<tr><td>PasswordHash</td><td>nvarchar(500)</td><td>Not Null</td><td>BCrypt hashed password (cost=12)</td></tr>
<tr><td>MFAEnabled</td><td>bit</td><td>Default: 0</td><td>Multi-factor auth flag for privileged roles</td></tr>
<tr><td>Status</td><td>nvarchar(20)</td><td>Not Null, Default: 'Active', Enum: <code>UserStatus</code></td><td>Active &verbar; Inactive &verbar; Suspended &verbar; Locked</td></tr>
<tr><td>CreatedAt</td><td>datetime2</td><td>Default: GETUTCDATE()</td><td>Account creation timestamp</td></tr>
<tr><td>UpdatedAt</td><td>datetime2</td><td>Nullable</td><td>Last profile update timestamp</td></tr>
</table>
<blockquote><strong>v10.1 Change:</strong> <code>RefreshToken</code> (nvarchar(500)) and <code>RefreshTokenExpiry</code> (datetime2) columns removed. A simpler JWT-to-session approach is used.</blockquote>

<p><strong>2. AuditLog</strong></p>
<p><em>Append-only audit trail. Immutable &mdash; no UPDATE or DELETE allowed.</em></p>
<table>
<tr><th>Column</th><th>Type</th><th>Constraints</th><th>Description</th></tr>
<tr><td>AuditID</td><td>int</td><td>PK, Identity</td><td>Auto-increment primary key</td></tr>
<tr><td>UserID</td><td>int</td><td>FK &rarr; User.UserID</td><td>User who performed the action</td></tr>
<tr><td>Action</td><td>nvarchar(100)</td><td>Not Null</td><td>Action performed</td></tr>
<tr><td>ResourceType</td><td>nvarchar(50)</td><td>Not Null</td><td>Entity type affected</td></tr>
<tr><td>ResourceID</td><td>int</td><td>Not Null</td><td>ID of the affected entity</td></tr>
<tr><td>DetailsJSON</td><td>nvarchar(max)</td><td>Nullable</td><td>JSON: action-specific context</td></tr>
<tr><td>Timestamp</td><td>datetime2</td><td>Default: GETUTCDATE()</td><td>When the action occurred</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>Module 2: Student Registry &amp; Admissions (SISService)</h3>

<p><strong>3. Applicant</strong></p>
<table>
<tr><th>Column</th><th>Type</th><th>Constraints</th><th>Description</th></tr>
<tr><td>ApplicantID</td><td>int</td><td>PK, Identity</td><td>Auto-increment primary key</td></tr>
<tr><td>Name</td><td>nvarchar(200)</td><td>Not Null</td><td>Applicant full name</td></tr>
<tr><td>DOB</td><td>date</td><td>Not Null</td><td>Date of birth</td></tr>
<tr><td>NationalID</td><td>nvarchar(50)</td><td>Nullable</td><td>Government ID number</td></tr>
<tr><td>ContactInfoJSON</td><td>nvarchar(max)</td><td>Nullable</td><td>JSON: {email, phone, address, emergencyContact}</td></tr>
<tr><td>ProgramApplied</td><td>nvarchar(100)</td><td>Not Null</td><td>Program/degree applied for</td></tr>
<tr><td>ApplicationStatus</td><td>nvarchar(30)</td><td>Not Null, Default: 'Submitted', Enum: <code>ApplicationStatus</code></td><td>Submitted &verbar; UnderReview &verbar; Accepted &verbar; Rejected &verbar; Waitlisted</td></tr>
<tr><td>SubmittedAt</td><td>datetime2</td><td>Default: GETUTCDATE()</td><td>Application submission date</td></tr>
<tr><td>DocumentsURIJSON</td><td>nvarchar(max)</td><td>Nullable</td><td>JSON: [{name, uri, sha256, uploadedAt}]</td></tr>
