<tr><td>Message</td><td>nvarchar(1000)</td><td>Not Null</td><td>Notification message</td></tr>
<tr><td>Category</td><td>nvarchar(30)</td><td>Not Null, Enum: <code>NotificationCategory</code></td><td>Enrollment &verbar; Grade &verbar; Finance &verbar; System &verbar; Academic</td></tr>
<tr><td>Severity</td><td>nvarchar(20)</td><td>Not Null, Default: 'Info', Enum: <code>NotificationSeverity</code></td><td>Info &verbar; Warning &verbar; Error &verbar; Critical</td></tr>
<tr><td>CreatedAt</td><td>datetime2</td><td>Default: GETUTCDATE()</td><td>Notification creation timestamp</td></tr>
<tr><td>ReadAt</td><td>datetime2</td><td>Nullable</td><td>When the notification was read (null = unread)</td></tr>
<tr><td>Status</td><td>nvarchar(20)</td><td>Not Null, Default: 'Active', Enum: <code>NotificationStatus</code></td><td>Active &verbar; Dismissed</td></tr>
</table>
<blockquote><strong>v10.1 Changes:</strong> NotificationCategory: Enrollment &verbar; Grade &verbar; Finance &verbar; System &verbar; Academic. NotificationSeverity: added Error. NotificationStatus: removed Expired.</blockquote>

<p><strong>25. Ticket</strong></p>
<table>
<tr><th>Column</th><th>Type</th><th>Constraints</th><th>Description</th></tr>
<tr><td>TicketID</td><td>int</td><td>PK, Identity</td><td>Auto-increment primary key</td></tr>
<tr><td>CreatedByFK</td><td>int</td><td>FK &rarr; User.UserID</td><td>User who submitted the ticket</td></tr>
<tr><td>AssignedToFK</td><td>int</td><td>FK &rarr; User.UserID, Nullable</td><td>Support staff assigned</td></tr>
<tr><td>Subject</td><td>nvarchar(200)</td><td>Not Null</td><td>Ticket subject line</td></tr>
<tr><td>Description</td><td>nvarchar(max)</td><td>Not Null</td><td>Detailed issue description</td></tr>
<tr><td>Priority</td><td>nvarchar(20)</td><td>Not Null, Default: 'Medium', Enum: <code>TicketPriority</code></td><td>Low &verbar; Medium &verbar; High &verbar; Critical</td></tr>
<tr><td>CreatedAt</td><td>datetime2</td><td>Default: GETUTCDATE()</td><td>Ticket creation timestamp</td></tr>
<tr><td>UpdatedAt</td><td>datetime2</td><td>Nullable</td><td>Last update timestamp</td></tr>
<tr><td>Status</td><td>nvarchar(20)</td><td>Not Null, Default: 'Open', Enum: <code>TicketStatus</code></td><td>Open &verbar; InProgress &verbar; Resolved &verbar; Closed</td></tr>
<tr><td>ResolutionURI</td><td>nvarchar(500)</td><td>Nullable</td><td>Resolution documentation URI</td></tr>
</table>

<h2>5.3 Design Notes</h2>
<p>&bull; <strong>DeleteBehavior:</strong> All foreign keys use <code>DeleteBehavior.NoAction</code> to prevent cascade issues in shared database.</p>
<p>&bull; <strong>ExcludeFromMigrations:</strong> Non-owned tables in each DbContext use <code>ExcludeFromMigrations()</code> to prevent duplicate schema creation.</p>
<p>&bull; <strong>Strongly-typed enums:</strong> All status, type, role, category, and method fields use C# enums with <code>HasConversion&lt;string&gt;().HasMaxLength(N)</code> in EF Core. Swagger displays human-readable string dropdowns via <code>JsonStringEnumConverter</code> + <code>EnumSchemaFilter</code>.</p>
<p>&bull; <strong>Media storage:</strong> Azure Blob Storage with SHA-256 checksums for tamper evidence.</p>
<p>&bull; <strong>Indexes:</strong> (StudentID, ProgramID), (CourseID, Term), (Timestamp) on AuditLog, (DueDate) on Invoice.</p>

<h2>5.6 Database Migration Strategy</h2>
<p>EduLearn uses a <strong>dedicated MigrationDbContext</strong> pattern. A single <code>EduLearn.DbMigrator</code> project contains one <code>MigrationDbContext</code> that maps all 25 entities with all FK constraints. This creates the entire database schema in one atomic migration &mdash; zero FK ordering issues.</p>
<p><strong>Why this pattern?</strong> Multiple services with cross-service FK dependencies cannot be migrated independently without FK ordering failures. The single-migrator pattern is used by production frameworks like ABP and is recommended by Microsoft for shared-database architectures.</p>
<p><strong>Migration command:</strong> <code>.\migrate-database.bat</code></p>
<blockquote><strong>v10.1 Change:</strong> The previous multi-step migration order (Auth &rarr; LMS &rarr; SIS &rarr; Finance &rarr; Notification &rarr; Analytics) has been replaced with this single-step DbMigrator approach.</blockquote>

